title: Signs, Symbols and Ornaments (Design Graphic Ebook).pdf
description:
pdf / English / 1982 / 180 pages / 14.9 MB

In the beginning was the sign. All peoples in all times and in all places have applied these signs in thousands of variations and combinations. The sign became a symbol. A symbol is a word or sign whenever it 'means' more than one sees at first glance" (C.G. Jung). The sign acquires a deeper meaning and takes the place of an abstract idea
